<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="463" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d463">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 661.119 Vessels/14</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Admiralty Counsel of the United States
                                    Shipping Board</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Huger</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-29"><hi rend="italic">March 29,
                                        1918</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Sir</hi>: The Shipping Board is negotiating
                                with the Russian Ambassador, and will this afternoon execute a
                                number of charter parties for the use of various vessels of the
                                Russian Volunteer Fleet. The following letter has been handed to us
                                as the authority for Mr. <persName>Medzikhovski</persName> to
                                execute the charter parties: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                    <p>I hereby authorize Mr. <persName>C. J.
                                            Medzikhovski</persName>, commercial attache to the
                                        Russian Embassy, to charter steamships of the Russian
                                        Volunteer Fleet to the United States Government on
                                        conditions which he may consider proper; to execute and sign
                                        charters and other necessary documents, his signature being
                                        applied on behalf of the Provisional Government of Russia.
                                            <persName corresp="#p_BBA1">Boris A.
                                            Bakhmeteff</persName>.</p>
                                </quote>
                            </p>
                            <p>…</p>
                            <p>Very truly yours,</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName><hi rend="smallcaps">Alfred
                                    Huger</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>